## Vulnerability Detective (Ensemble)

The CLI includes a multi-model Vulnerability Detective system that uses an ensemble of classifiers to identify potential safety issues in model interactions. The system is designed for classification only and never generates or elaborates on harmful content.

### Usage

```bash
# Install with development dependencies
make install-dev

# Run example detection
make run-example

# Or run directly with custom options
cosmosapien detect-vuln \
  --input examples/sample.json \
  --config cosmosapien/config/redteam.yaml \
  --ensemble risk_max \
  --backend local_rules openai
```

### Configuration

Default configuration in `cosmosapien/config/redteam.yaml`:

```yaml
models:
  - type: local_rules
  - type: openai
    name: gpt-4  # or your default model
ensemble: risk_max
```

### Example Output

```json
{
  "is_vulnerability": true,
  "primary_category": "BIO",
  "secondary_categories": ["CYA"],
  "severity": "high",
  "rationale": "Content contains potential biological hazard instructions",
  "evidence_quotes": ["[...] incubate [...] household equipment [...]"],
  "safe_fix_summary": "Content requires revision to remove harmful elements",
  "manipulation_signals": ["MISDIRECTION", "MINIMIZATION"]
}
```

### Safety Note

The Vulnerability Detective is designed for classification purposes only. It identifies and categorizes potential safety issues without generating, storing, or transmitting any harmful operational details. All evidence snippets are automatically masked to prevent sensitive information disclosure.
